# Local credential store for MolCrawl workflows.
#
# 1. Copy this file to ".env" at the repo root:
#      cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit ".env" with real credentials. ".env" is gitignored
#    (see ".gitignore" :: ``.env*``); .env.example is the only file
#    in this family that is meant to be committed.
#
# 3. Re-run any workflow under workflows/. The auto-loader in
#    workflows/common_functions.sh sources .env at repo root if
#    present, falling back to ~/.config/molcrawl/.env. All variables
#    set in .env become available as exported env vars.
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit a populated .env. Double-check ``git status``
# before pushing — any line beginning with ``A  .env`` (added file)
# means you are about to leak credentials.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# COSMIC — somatic-variant evaluator (eval-data-cosmic.sh)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Register at https://cancer.sanger.ac.uk/cosmic and accept the
# academic / commercial license. Then fill these:
# COSMIC_EMAIL=
# COSMIC_PASSWORD=
# COSMIC_VERSION=v100
# COSMIC_GENOME=GRCh38

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# OMIM — gene–disease association evaluator (eval-data-omim.sh)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Register at https://www.omim.org/api and submit a brief academic
# justification. Approval typically takes ~1 business day; the API key
# arrives by email and looks like ``ABC1234567890ABC``.
# OMIM_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# HuggingFace — gated datasets and models (e.g. zhihan1996/DNABERT_2)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign in at https://huggingface.co, accept any gated-dataset terms
# you need access to, then create a Read-scope token at
# https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens.
# HF_TOKEN=
